Raw dev notes -- RAG Pipelines: Cleaning Source Material for AI Knowledge Bases (Feb-March 2026)

Built two RAG preparation pipelines to clean and structure source materials for
an AI knowledge base platform. The main challenge: raw source files are messy
and the platform has strict upload limits.

Pipeline stages:
- Standardize formats (PDF, DOCX, HTML -> clean Markdown)
- Assess RAG-readiness and overlap between sources
- LLM-based cleanup via Gemini API (async concurrent chunk processing)
- Quality gate to prevent hallucination/expansion (105% length limit)
- Batch into upload-sized packages with proper heading separators

Gemini cleanup pipeline learnings:
- Thinking mode + anti-hallucination prompt rules are essential
- Quality gate at 105% caught cases where the model was expanding or paraphrasing
- Split-retry for failed chunks worked better than increasing chunk size
- Had to block formula reconstruction -- the model kept 'fixing' math notation
- Cross-file event loop bug: must reset SDK client between asyncio.run() calls

Also built a benchmark comparing different AI platforms on Hebrew-language questions
with ground-truth answers. Interesting differences in how each handles Hebrew text.

Archived 75 one-off scripts during the codebase reorganization. Felt good to clean up.

